    <solution><p>We can make a substitution <m>z = (x+1)^2\text{.}</m>  Then, we have <m>{8z - 3z^2 +5 = 0}\text{.}</m>  We can re-write this as <m>{3z^2 - 8z - 5 = 0.}</m></p>
<p>We can use the quadratic formula:</p>
<p><me>z = \frac{8 \pm \sqrt{64 + 60}}{6} \approx -0.52259, 3.18926.</me></p>
<p>Recall that <m>z=(x+1)^2\text{.}</m>  So, <m>(x+1)^2 = -0.52259</m> or <m>(x+1)^2 = 3.18926.</m> This first gives non-real solutions. Solving <m>(x+1)^2 = 3.18926</m> gives <m>x \approx -2.78585</m> or <m>x \approx 0.78585.</m></p>
</solution>
